<BaseLayout title="What Is a LoRA Model?" description="A beginner-friendly explanation of LoRA models for image generation." canonicalPath="/lora/what-is-lora/"><article class="content-section article-body"><h1>What Is a LoRA Model?</h1><p>A LoRA is a compact add-on model that nudges a larger image model toward a focused concept. It may represent an original character design, a lawful object class, a visual style, or a narrow production need.</p><p>For this site, LoRA guidance is limited to all-ages, lawful, permission-safe workflows. Do not train on private people, celebrities, copied characters, or material you do not have the right to use.</p></article></BaseLayout>
